AB  - The evolution of global trade has necessitated a paradigm shift in port operations to optimise movement of goods/information within maritime industry through digitally enhanced systems. However, ports in developing countries face challenges including need for implementation framework, cybersecurity threats, inter-system interoperability, and regulatory compliance. To address these challenges, this study explores smart port evolution, components, and benefits, to develop Smart Port Concept Implementation (SPCI) framework, emphasising operational optimisation and sustainability. Using comprehensive literature review, 65 articles were analyzed to identify the challenges and emerging future trends of the smart port concept. The research reveals that while smart ports offer transformative benefits, however, challenges such as high capital investment, integration issues, and labour gaps still remain. Future developments in smart ports will include fully automated operations, seamless digital ecosystems, green infrastructure, climate resilience, smart city integration, and predictive operations. These advancements require coordinated efforts among policymakers, industry stakeholders, and technology providers to enable a sustainable and inclusive transition toward smart port ecosystems. © 2025 Informa UK Limited, trading as Taylor & Francis Group.
